cs.CR, cs.HC, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.CY 

This paper deals with continuous authentication for smartphones, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR). The use of application usage data and Hidden Markov Models (HMMs) also suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and signal processing (cs.SI). Additionally, the focus on user behavior and interaction with the smartphone suggests a connection to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of unforeseen events on user verification, which could be relevant to cybersecurity (cs.CY).
